posts.name: Benjamin Miller
posts.cooked: We got a base SwerveDrive (mk4i) done and tested during the off-season. So now we update the robo-rio and wpilib and game tools to 2023 and the code deployed fine but the driver station is saying no code. There are no errors on deploy.

posts.name: Mark McLeod
posts.cooked: Then your code is crashing at runtime. The most common cause is using something before it has been instantiated. The answers will be in the console messages and log, so take a look there.

posts.name: Chris Gerth
posts.cooked: The driver station or RioLog should have more print statements. This document lists out some info on how to interpret errors in those print statements to poitn you to the problematic lines of code

link_counts.title: Reading Stacktraces — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation

posts.name: MetabolicCloth
posts.cooked: Check for null pointer errors, likely something isn’t initializing in the right order or you’re trying to access a device before it was initialized. The driver station, above the console on the right theres a gear, click it and view console. That should give you more insight into where the code is crashing.

posts.name: Ishaan Sareen
posts.cooked: My team had this issue yesterday. We resolved it by updating the vendordeps files which weren’t up to date.
